<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-11-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-11-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="452" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d452">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72/2322C</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the German Ambassador</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bernstorff</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-11-24">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 24, 1915</hi>.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Ambassador</hi>: I have not heard from
                            you since our conversation in regard to the <hi rend="italic">Lusitania</hi> case. I hope that you have been able to accomplish
                            something. It is imperative that we should reach a speedy settlement of
                            this controversy for the reasons which I stated to you when we talked
                            the matter over. I hope that a conclusion may be reached within a very
                            few days.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>